TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Liste des defaults (FRAM, FLASH, RTC, Vbatt, Pi, Pe, SBE41-Cutoff, SBE41-Offset, GPS, Payload, Sensor(xxx), Transmitter)
TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Auto-test is performed at the beginning of the mission: Flag 0 = Problem, 1 = OK)

The failed flag bits (1 if failed, 0 otherwise) set during the initial check are provided in reverse order for: FRAM, FLASH, RTC, Vbatt, Pi, Pe, SBE41-Cutoff, SBE41-Offset, GPS, Payload, Sensor, Transmitter (see float manual for details).
Alarm raised when a low level of the battery is detected (the check is done without any load on the battery).
Alarm raised when a low level of the battery is detected (the check is done with load on the battery, i.e. pump action at depth).
Alarm raised when external pressure is too low.
Alarm raised when external pressure is too high.
Alarm raised when the external pressure sensor reports abnormal number of successive errors.
Alarm raised when a vertical speed anomaly is detected by the buoyancy management system.
Alarm raised when internal pressure is too high.
Alarm when water is detected inside one of the sensors.
Alarm raised when the float is hanged during ascent.
Alarm raised when the descent speed is too high and the float brakes.
Alarm raised when the system fails.

Alarm raised when the GPS fails.
Alarm raised when the hydraulic engine fails.
Alarm raised when the Analog to Digital Converter fails.
Alarm raised when a file cannot be transmitted.
Alarm raised when the Real Time Clock fails.
Alarm raised when the pressure switch fails.
Alarm raised when the float switches to the End Of Life mode. When reported as a NUMBER, it provides the reason of the End Of Life (see float manual for details).
